    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>About Wonta Rural Development Association</h2>

      <p>
        Wonta Rural Development Association is committed to empowering rural communities by creating sustainable 
        development programs that improve education, healthcare, agriculture, and economic opportunities.
      </p>

      <p>
        We work hand-in-hand with local leaders and families to understand their needs and build solutions that bring 
        long-term, meaningful change to underserved communities.
      </p>

      <!-- Moving Images Gallery (Only one image now) -->
      <div class="moving-gallery">
        <img id="about-image2" src="/images/about2.jpg" alt="Education Development Program">
      </div>

      <p>
        Through collaboration, innovation, and community-driven planning, we are dedicated to making rural communities 
        stronger, healthier, and more resilient.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h3>Our Mission</h3>
      <p>
        To support and uplift rural communities through sustainable development initiatives that improve education, 
        health, agriculture, and income generation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h3>Our Vision</h3>
      <p>
        A future where every rural community has access to equal opportunities, essential services, and the resources 
        required for long-term well-being.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h3>What We Do</h3>

      <ul class="about-list">
        <li><strong>Education:</strong> School support, teacher training, and youth development programs.</li>
        <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Medical outreach, health education, and community clinics.</li>
        <li><strong>Agriculture:</strong> Farmer training, irrigation systems, and sustainable farming support.</li>
        <li><strong>Women Empowerment:</strong> Skills training, financial inclusion, and leadership initiatives.</li>
        <li><strong>Community Development:</strong> Clean water access, environmental protection, and local capacity building.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </main>

